About the job

Company Overview: Miko is a Mumbai based advanced consumer robotics innovation lab

passionate about bringing the best of technology to young learners everywhere and home to some of the world’s leading engineers, mathematicians, teachers and psychologists. Our robots have been designed for the age group of 5-10 and the company’s flagship product, Miko 3, is the first robot that uses playful, conversational learning to educate, engage and entertain kids and is best-selling in the US, UK and UAE besides India.




Excellent in Electronic Knowledge / Product Design/ Product Manufacture.




Department:

ELECTRONICS AMD EMBEDDED

Position Title:

VP/Head - Electronics Hardware Design Architect

KEY PURPOSE OF THE JOB (POSITION SUMMARY)

We are looking for a responsible Electronics Hardware Architect to mainly focus on Hardware Platform Innovation. In this role, the Hardware Architect will closely work with multiple teams and groups including Product Development, Product Management, Sourcing, Product Marketing and Quality Assurance, etc.

Experience – 15+ years Only Can apply

ROLES & RESPONSIBILITIES

· Lead technical roadmap development for company products; Product level work.

· Work closely with Product marketing to deliver the fast prototype to valid the meaningful innovation in field; Modularize existing products electronics design; Conduct design review for electronics engineering part; Collaborate with cross functional teams to develop and qualify products to meet specification, reliability and regulatory;

· Responsible for the New-Development and enhancement of HW Concepts; HW-Architecture;

· Description of Interfaces;

· Dimensioning of electronic circuits;

· Tolerance and Lifetime Calculations;

· Incorporation and Test of electronic circuits;

· Definition of Test Procedures;

· Responsible for the implementation of external and internal requirements in our HW- System;

· Responsible for evaluations of Norms, Standards and Customer Requirements;

· Secure Product Robustness, apply standards; Drive Innovations.




REQUIRED SKILLS

· Extensive knowledge of IOT architectures;

· Should know how to code MCU and how cloud system works;

· Highly developed hardware design skills;

· Experience in managing direct subordinates, able to hire, coach and develop AD (advance develop) teams;

· Should have a creative and curiosity way of working leading to continuous improvements;

· Must be open minded and willing to accept new challenges;

· Strong written and oral communication skills.

EDUCATION AND EXPERIENCE REQUIRED:

· Education: Bachelor / Master in Electronics Engineering

· Experience: 8 to 12 years of relevant experience.




Regards

Gagandeep Kaur

gagan.kaur@miko.ai

